column5: WTG guys,  looks like a nasty drive out.  hummm perch you say..
Good stuff !  Another hundred yards out and you'd have been right on Whitie/Laker money ...

Ya that is odd that you found only 8inches of ice.  I was out on Simcoe on Saturday and in both locations I set up, I was sitting over 55 to 60 feet of water and had to drill through easily 16 to 18inches of ice!  Trust me...I have the sore shoulders and arms to prove it!  Ab
Paul isn't dumb.... and knows how to pick a thin spot to save his arms! lol

As mentioned in my previous thread, we planned to meet up with Muskybill in Innisfil today.  The drive up was not pretty and as soon as we got on the highway we were behind the plows.  Not a bad thing, but it made a slow drive even slower.    We found Bill right off the bat already set up in about 45 feet of water, so we set up and started fishing.  The snow did not let up most of the day, as shown in this pic of Paul, who BTW, got the first fish AND outfished us all    Bill doing a jig and having a laugh.    Visibility was low, can't even see Fox Island, but there were alot of people out there.    Couple action shots of Bill catching some Perch.      There was about 8 inches where we fished.  Which was a bit unnerving when a truck kept driving by and making the ice crack and moan    Our take home for the day    AND, the drive home......      We got one for Team 5 tho    It was a pleasure Bill.  Look forward to seeing you at the Tyler Fundraiser.  Joey
Great stuff Joey! Paul caught a fish eh... no picture... lol  Only 8 inches of ice... figured there'd be more by now. Then again I thought the same of GBay today... was only 9/10 inches.

it was a nasty day out there I turned back, never made it to Waynes  glad to see you guys made it there and back safely  what's with Paul catching fish on the ice my whole universe is going  upside down ....LOL

Great report and pics Hosette!!!  ... I've been waiting for this report all day!!!  Good on Paul for catching and outfishing y'all today!... every Dawg has his day yanno!!!  What's that stuff on Bills face???... did he forget to wash again?  Did y'all see Jose?... or did he wimp out?  That volcanic ash is pretty nasty this time of year eh?  That killer Perch is a good start to the tourney!!!

I got there just after 6:30am and was blasted by snow. I walked about 400 feet and drilled my first and only hole. Set up my hut and began to fish right off the bat started to catch fish. I was on 15 feet 15 to 20 feet of water and did well all morning long. I did keep my eye out for Bill and Joey but never did see much. As i was leaving i saw well over 200 huts on the ice and people just kept coming in.  Good to see you guys hit some fish and will see you at the fishing for Tyler on the 14th.
Ya, I just read your report, I don't blame you.  I questioned why we were out there on the road a few times.  It was not fun.   Wayne, that's not much ice at all  Joey
J ,There are times when Im thankful they are infront of me. Control. Nice perchies.
What a bummer we missed you.  We thought you had a change of heart due to the weather.  Joey
nice report glad to see you got fish...

I was the second Person on the ice in the morning from the parking lot but by the looks of it i was the very first hut you would see closes to the shore. One thing i try never to back down when it comes to fishing even if it means driving in a blizarred. I would have loved to stay longer but at 10:30 i packed it in and headed home for a birthday party.  For all that fished with out huts i have to say you are true die hards and my hat goes off to you all.

Yup, the snow never let up, from some point yesterday afternoon....  Definitely took a lot longer to reach Innisfil than I had planned. I had one lane to drive in for 101.2 kms, according to my trip metre. I believe I hit the parking lot at 7:30, & I couldn't believe I'd already been up for 3 hours, & STILL hadn't cut my first hole!  Anyways, I walked out a bit further than I usually do at Innisfil. You can see someone's headlights from the parking lot on shore in the background...    I kept my eyes open for Aile Goby, Joey or Paul, but the snow was really coming down, & I knew I'd be in tough to find anyone. I cut my first hole, applied my 3 minnow spread (one on bottom, one a foot up & one,  two feet) & before I could get up to cut my 2nd hole, I had my first Perch of 2009 landed, & sent back. I got my 2nd hole cut, but before I could send down the breakfast invitations, I heard someone say "There's Bill right there!", & sure enough, Joey & Paul had found me! After a brief poop chat, Paul got some holes cut, & we were all fishin'...    Twice, I caught 2 at a time...    But the biggest of the day went to Joey with this chumbawumba...    I had to pack it in at noon, but it was a fun & busy morning to be sure. Too bad we couldn't see you Aile Goby, next time for sure. As always Joey & Paul, thanks for the great company, & see you at the Tyler Tourney, or sooner....
Great report and pics as well Bill!!!  Good to see ya get out!!!
A fish for the OFC 2009 Tourny already . Good job, perch are soo yummy, enjoy.  Thanks for sharing!
Great report gang...Joey, nice fish!!!  Good to see some fish are being caught in the area...hope they're still there in a couple of weeks  Maureen

Great report and pics Joey  Looks like you guys had a good time and landed some real nice chunky ones.... congratulations I guess your cat will have another perch feast sushi style Thanks for sharing Leechman
Great pics btw, Joey, I LOVE the action shot....

Hey, thanks for the report. I'm surprised there isn't more ice there. We were out on wed/thurs mid lake and there was at least 12" everywhere. I actually measured it with a tape too!! One spot had almost 15"!!  Good on ya's for getting out there today, it was a nasty day to say the least!!  Sinker
Great report Joey to bad you guys missed hooking up with Jose so you say Paul got a fish any proof the only picture i see of Paul is standing there try to keep warm lol
Good going Joey.   8" of ice and there's a truck out on it....CRAZY!!!!!!    How was supper.?..those perch look big!   cheers    Simon
AttaGrrl, JoAnne.
wow, good of you to brave those conditions and get a nice report for us!  thanks!
Looked miserably fun out there.  Good fishing Joey and Co.
woooooo Team 5 on the boat already!!!  Great job!
Great report Joey et al. I'm really glad y'all got home safely in that nasty weather.

Good stuff Joey!!  Was out in Innisfil on Saturday also... Looks like we shoulda, woulda, coulda been after perch.  You outta gimme a hollah next time you and Paul hit Simcoe...  I'd love to add to the fray!  cheers sugar beet. HD
